# EmailJS Configuration
# Sign up at https://www.emailjs.com/ to get these values

# Your EmailJS Service ID
# Get this from EmailJS Dashboard > Email Services
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=service_xxxxxxx

# Your EmailJS Template ID  
# Get this from EmailJS Dashboard > Email Templates
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=template_xxxxxxx

# Your EmailJS Public Key
# Get this from EmailJS Dashboard > Account > API Keys
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Instructions:
# 1. Sign up for free at https://www.emailjs.com/
# 2. Create an Email Service (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
# 3. Create an Email Template with these variables:
#    - {{to_email}} - Recipient email
#    - {{to_name}} - Recipient name
#    - {{from_name}} - Patient name
#    - {{from_email}} - Patient email
#    - {{record_count}} - Number of records
#    - {{date_range}} - Date range of records
#    - {{summary}} - Records summary
#    - {{share_link}} - Share link (if applicable)
#    - {{attachment}} - PDF attachment (base64)
# 4. Copy your Service ID, Template ID, and Public Key
# 5. Create a .env file and add these values
# 6. Restart your development server

# Example Template HTML:
# Subject: Health Records from {{from_name}}
# 
# Dear {{to_name}},
# 
# {{from_name}} ({{from_email}}) has shared {{record_count}} health records with you.
# 
# Date Range: {{date_range}}
# 
# Summary:
# {{summary}}
# 
# Please find the attached PDF for complete details.
# 
# This email contains protected health information.
# 
# Best regards,
# Revado Health App